devdoc.author: Tim Coulter <tim.coulter@consensys.net>, Piper Merriam <pipermerriam@gmail.com>

getAllPackageIds(uint256,uint256).details: Returns a slice of the array of all package hashes for the named package.

params.offset: The starting index for the slice.

getNumPackages().details: Return the total number of packages

params.nameHash: The name hash to look up.

getPackageName(bytes32).details: Returns the package name for the given namehash

params.nameHash: The name hash to look up.

getPackageNameHash(uint256).details: Returns package namehash at the provided index from the set of all known name hashes.

params.idx: The index of the package name hash to retrieve.

hashName(string).details: Returns name hash for a given package name.

packageExists(bytes32).details: Query the existence of a package with the given name.  Returns boolean indicating whether the package exists.

params.nameHash: The name hash of a package.

removePackage(bytes32,string).details: Removes a package from the package db.  Packages with existing releases may not be removed.  Returns success.

params.nameHash: The name hash of a package.

setPackage(string).details: Creates or updates a release for a package.  Returns success.

setPackageOwner(bytes32,address).details: Sets the owner of a package to the provided address.  Returns success.

params.nameHash: The name hash of a package.
params.newPackageOwner: The address of the new owner.

generateReleaseId(string,string).details: Returns release id that *would* be generated for a name and version pair on `release`.

getAllPackageIds(uint256,uint256).details: Returns a slice of the array of all package hashes for the named package.

params.offset: The starting index for the slice.

getAllReleaseIds(string,uint256,uint256).details: Returns a slice of the array of all package hashes for the named package.

params.offset: The starting index for the slice.

getPackageDb().details: Returns the address of the packageDb

getPackageName(bytes32).details: Retrieves the name for the given name hash.

params.packageId: The name hash of package to lookup the name for.

getReleaseData(bytes32).details: Returns the release data for the release associated with the given release hash.

getReleaseDb().details: Returns the address of the releaseDb

getReleaseId(string,string).details: Returns the release id for a given name and version pair if present on registry.

getReleaseValidator().details: Returns the address of the releaseValidator

numPackageIds().details: Returns the number of packages stored on the registry

numReleaseIds(string).details: Returns the number of releases for a given package name on the registry

packageExists(string).details: Query the existence of a package with the given name.  Returns boolean indicating whether the package exists.

release(string,string,string).details: Creates a a new release for the named package.  If this is the first release for the given package then this will also assign msg.sender as the owner of the package.  Returns success.

params.manifestURI: The URI for the release manifest for this release.

releaseExists(string,string).details: Query the existence of a release at the provided version for the named package.  Returns boolean indicating whether such a release exists.

setPackageDb(address).details: Sets the address of the PackageDb contract.

params.newPackageDb: The address to set for the PackageDb.

setReleaseDb(address).details: Sets the address of the ReleaseDb contract.

getAllPackageIds(uint256,uint256).details: Returns a slice of the array of all package ids for the named package.

params.offset: The starting index for the slice.

getAllReleaseIds(string,uint256,uint256).details: Returns a slice of the array of all release hashes for the named package.

params.offset: The starting index for the slice.

getPackageName(bytes32).details: Returns the string name of the package associated with a package id

params.packageId: The package id to look up

getReleaseData(bytes32).details: Returns the package data for a release.

getReleaseId(string,string).details: Returns the release id for a given name and version pair if present on registry.

numPackageIds().details: Returns the number of packages stored on the registry

numReleaseIds(string).details: Returns the number of releases for a given package name on the registry

release(string,string,string).details: Creates a a new release for the named package.

params.manifestURI: The URI for the release manifest for this release.

devdoc.title: EIP 1319 Smart Contract Package Registry Interface

devdoc.author: Tim Coulter <tim.coulter@consensys.net>, Piper Merriam <pipermerriam@gmail.com>

getAllReleaseIds(bytes32,uint256,uint256.details: Returns a slice of the array of all releases hashes for the named package.

params.offset: The starting index for the slice.

getManifestURI(bytes32).details: Returns the URI of the release manifest for the given release hash.

getNumReleasesForNameHash(bytes32).details: Get the total number of releases

getReleaseData(bytes32).details: Returns the releaseData for the given release has a package.

getReleaseIdForNameHash(bytes32,uint256).details: Release hash for a Package at a given index

params.idx: The index of the release hash to retrieve.

getVersion(bytes32).details: Returns string version identifier from the version of the given release hash.

hashRelease(bytes32,bytes32).details: Returns release hash for the given release

params.nameHash: The name hash of the package name.
params.versionHash: The version hash for the release version.

hashVersion(string).details: Returns version hash for the given semver version.

releaseExisted(bytes32).details: Query the past existence of a release at the provided version for a package.  Returns boolean indicating whether such a release ever existed.

releaseExists(bytes32).details: Query the existence of a release at the provided version for a package.  Returns boolean indicating whether such a release exists.

removeRelease(bytes32,string).details: Removes a release from a package.  Returns success.

params.reason: Explanation for why the removal happened.
params.releaseId: The release hash to be removed

setRelease(bytes32,bytes32,string).details: Creates or updates a release for a package.  Returns success.

params.manifestURI: The URI for the release manifest for this release.
params.nameHash: The name hash of the package.
params.versionHash: The version hash for the release version.

setVersion(string).details: Adds the given version to the local version database.  Returns the versionHash for the provided version.

versionExists(bytes32).details: Query the existence of the provided version in the recorded versions.  Returns boolean indicating whether such a version exists.
